        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Richmond, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Richmond, Harris Ferry, Berea, Round Hill, Caleast, Duluth,
Peytontown, Vianna, Bighill, and Redhouse.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
